00:45:08.560 --> 00:45:10.159
I'm curious how data privacy factors

00:45:10.159 --> 00:45:12.080
into your criteria of responsible use.

00:45:12.080 --> 00:45:13.919
I've heard some concerns about open AI sharing info.

00:45:13.919 --> 00:45:16.439
You should be concerned about open AI sharing info

00:45:16.439 --> 00:45:18.280
unless you have an enterprise agreement with them

00:45:18.280 --> 00:45:20.080
that has zero data retention.

00:45:20.080 --> 00:45:21.479
That being said, it's very easy

00:45:21.479 --> 00:45:24.560
to get a zero data retention agreement

00:45:24.560 --> 00:45:26.280
for all of the major providers.

00:45:26.320 --> 00:45:27.639
And they have a lot to lose

00:45:27.639 --> 00:45:31.239
if you are under that kind of regime with them

00:45:31.239 --> 00:45:33.239
and they leak your information.

00:45:33.239 --> 00:45:35.199
So I think it's important to know

00:45:35.199 --> 00:45:37.120
what the data privacy policies are

00:45:37.120 --> 00:45:39.120
of the models that you're connecting to.

00:45:39.120 --> 00:45:42.879
But if you're on Bedrock, if you're on Azure AI,

00:45:42.879 --> 00:45:46.280
I believe that they default to no data retained.

00:45:46.280 --> 00:45:49.239
So I think that the data privacy issue

00:45:49.239 --> 00:45:50.800
is far overblown these days.

